# Project: Agent Skills - Claude Code Agent Skills Monorepo

## Structure
This monorepo uses pnpm workspaces with the following structure:

```
packages/
└── analysis-agent/
    ├── agents/       # Claude Code and Copilot agents
    ├── skills/       # Reusable SKILL.md files
    ├── scripts/      # CLI scripts for analysis
    ├── templates/    # Configuration templates
    └── .agentrc.json # Package metadata
```

## Skills
Each skill is a `SKILL.md` file with the following frontmatter:

```markdown
---
name: skill-name
description: What this skill does
compatibility: What it requires
user-invokable: true/false
argument-hint: How to use it
metadata:
  author: author-name
  version: "1.0"
---
```

## Usage
To use skills in another project:
1. Copy `packages/analysis-agent/.agent` to your project
2. Run `bash .agent/scripts/setup.sh`
3. Run `pnpm install`

## Agent Integration
Agents go in `.claude/agents/` or `.github/agents/` and reference skills via paths.
